data.enText: making people have a good opinion of sb/sth

data.chText: 她给他的父母留下了好印象。
data.enText: She made a favourable impression on his parents.

data.chText: 传记刻画出了他的正面形象。
data.enText: The biography shows him in a favourable light.
positive and showing your good opinion of sb/sth
good for sth and making it likely to be successful or have an advantage

data.chText: 协议条款对双方都有利。
data.enText: The terms of the agreement are favourable to both sides.
fairly good and not too expensive

data.chText: 他们提出以十分优惠的条件贷款给我。
data.enText: They offered me a loan on very favourable terms .

data.chText: 他对你的工作十分赞赏。
data.enText: He speaks very favourably of your work.

data.chText: 这些数字比去年的好多了。
data.enText: These figures compare favourably with last year's.

data.chText: 她的工作给我留下了很好的印象。
data.enText: I was very favourably impressed with her work.

ex.chText: 该植物在适宜的条件下会结出果子。
ex.enText: This plant will produce fruits under favourable conditions.

ex.chText: 细菌在适当的条件下繁殖很快。
ex.enText: Bacteria multiply quickly under favourable conditions.

ex.chText: 在有利于海外投资的国际环境下，这个公司获得了巨额的利润。
ex.enText: The company has made a huge profit in an international environment that is favourable to overseas investment.

synonyms.bx: 指有利于某事发生或成功的。

ex.enText: This contract is advantageous to the owners.

ex.chText: 你的对手现在处于有利地位，所以你最好更谨慎一些。
ex.enText: You'd better be more cautious, as your rival is in an advantageous position.

synonyms.bx: 指对某人、某种情况等有好处或有帮助的。

ex.chText: 这些蔬菜对人们的健康有好处。
ex.enText: These vegetables have a positive effect on people's health.

ex.chText: 海外留学对他来说是一种有益的经历。
ex.enText: Studying overseas has been a positive experience for him.

synonyms.bx: 指积极的、良好的或有所助益的。

tr: presaging or likely to bring good luck
example: a favorable time to ask for a raise
a prosperous moment to make a decision

tr: occurring at a convenient or suitable time
example: an opportune time to receive guests

tr: (of winds or weather) tending to promote or facilitate
example: the days were fair and the winds were favorable

value.boxr_value: in AM, use 美国英语用 favorable

value.def: If your opinion or your reaction is favourable to something, you agree with it and approve of it.

example.ex: His recently completed chapel for Fitzwilliam is attracting favourable comment...
example.tran: 他最近为菲茨威廉建成的小教堂赢得了好评。

example.ex: The commission is cautiously favourable to Austrian membership, foreseeing few economic problems.
example.tran: 没有预见到什么经济问题，委员会谨慎地赞同吸收奥地利为会员。

example.ex: He listened intently, and responded favourably to both my suggestions...
example.tran: 他听得很专注，对我的两个建议都表示赞成。

example.ex: He was quite favourably impressed with the new French commander.
example.tran: 他对新的法国指挥官印象很好。

value.def: If something makes a favourable impression on you or is favourable to you, you like it and approve of it.

example.ex: His ability to talk tough while eating fast made a favourable impression on his dining companions...
example.tran: 他能一面快速地吃饭,一面言辞强硬地说话，给同他一起就餐的人留下了很好的印象。

value.tran: 良好的;肯定的;讨人喜欢的

value.def: Favourable conditions make something more likely to succeed or seem more attractive.

example.ex: It's believed the conditions in which the elections are being held are too favourable to the government.
example.tran: 人们认为举行选举的条件对政府过于有利。

example.ex: These terms were favourable to India.
Japan is thus favourably placed to maintain its lead as the most successful manufacturing nation.
example.tran: 这样，作为头号制造业强国，日本在保持其领先地位方面十分有利。

value.def: If you make a favourable comparison between two things, you say that the first is better than or as good as the second.

example.ex: The film bears favourable technical comparison with Hollywood productions costing 10 times as much.
example.tran: 该片与耗资为其 10 倍的好莱坞制作相比在技术上毫不逊色。

example.ex: Britain's overall road safety record compares favourably with that of other European countries.
example.tran: 英国整体的道路安全状况同其他欧洲国家相比毫不逊色。
